    "body": "### Problem\n\nIf `:startinsert` is executed from a autocommand or `nvim_buf_call`/`nvim_win_call`, it will not start insert mode in that buffer/window, but in whatever is the 'user current' buffer/window.\r\n\r\nA common way to reproduce this is by having a `TermOpen` autocommand that executes `startinsert`, such as shown in [the documentation for `:terminal`](https://neovim.io/doc/user/various.html#%3Aterminal), and opening a terminal buffer without switching to it, such as when opening multiple windows using `-o` / `-O`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nminimal.lua:\r\n```lua\r\nvim.cmd('au TermOpen * startinsert')\r\n```\r\n\r\nRun `nvim -u minimal.lua -O foo term://sh`\r\n\r\nObserve that insert mode is started in the `foo` buffer, not the terminal buffer.\r\n\r\nWrapping the call to `startinsert` in a call to `nvim_buf_call` or `nvim_win_call` furthermore does not work\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('TermOpen', {\r\n    callback = function(event)\r\n        vim.api.nvim_buf_call(event.buf, vim.cmd.startinsert)\r\n    end\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nAdditional oddity:\r\n\r\n`nvim -u NONE -O foo term://sh +'2bufdo set buftype?'` does print `buftype=terminal`, as one would expect, but also causes the leftmost window to also show the terminal buffer instead of the `foo` buffer. This behaviour appears to be shared by `vim` however and occurs even with regular buffers. The same does not occur with `:windo`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nInsert mode should be started in the buffer that the autocommand is being executed for, or the window/buffer that is the current API context.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-670+g3bcd5624b\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nvim -u minimal.vim -O foo bar +'2bufdo terminal ++curwin' does not reproduce it due to immediately becomming the active window.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20240203-110809-5046fc22\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\n`neovim-nightly-bin` AUR package (downloads latest GitHub release)",
